The paper deals with algorithms for detecting and counting patterns in planar graphs, which are topics that are commonly studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of balanced cycle separators and inclusion-exclusion arguments also suggests a connection to the area of graph algorithms and algorithmic graph theory. Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely as they deal directly with graph algorithms and data structures, while cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.GT are also relevant but may be slightly less likely as they are broader categories that encompass a wider range of topics.
